Mathira MP hopeful Cathy Irungu (pictured) has urged the government to repair roads, especially in Konyu ward. She said the 10km Ndima-Karima road has been in a deplorable state for years.Irungu spoke in Kiamabara ward on Friday during the burial of politician Ituu Ngacha. We don t have even a single kilometre of tarmarcked road in some places, she said.